<HEAD>Newborn Kidnapped From Hospital Found Healthy A Week Later</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRASSE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 9-day-old baby taken from his mother's hospital room last week has been found in the home of a woman depressed following a recent miscarriage, police said <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Salah </PERSON> appeared to be in perfect health when he was found Tuesday, polce said. <PERSON> Daniele </PERSON> <PERSON> Imbert </PERSON>, 43, and her common-law husband identified only as Mr. Lazur were being held for questioning but were not immediately charged. Police sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said she at first claimed the boy was her own, but under questioning admitted she had taken him from his mother's hospital room, three days after his birth. The mother, <PERSON> Latifa </PERSON> <PERSON> Salah </PERSON>, reported that <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> disappeared last Wednesday from his cradle in her room in the maternity ward at the <LOCATION> Grasse </LOCATION> hospital while she was taking a shower. Witnesses reported seeing a woman who appeared to be in her 40s carrying a baby out of the hospital at about that time, and police distributed a composite sketch. Neighbors of <PERSON> Daniele </PERSON> <PERSON> Imbert </PERSON> spotted the resemblance and alerted authorities. Police sources said the woman in custody had a miscarriage in June, and wanted a child desperately.
