 who played <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> during the debate preparation His aides have been conducting briefings along with question-and-answer sessions since last week. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Prosperi </PERSON>, <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>'s spokesman, said much of the area they had focused on involved attacks that were anticipated from <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON>. Polls have indicated that voters have doubts about <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>'s qualifications, but <PERSON> Prosperi </PERSON> resisted suggestions that tonight's debate could have a critical effect on the `` This is only part of the campaign. There's a continuous debate every day and there will be until Nov. 8,'' he said. `` The debate will be an important part of it, but it's not the end-all.''
