ed in peace talks. <PERSON> Aziz </PERSON>'s speech was moved up at his request from its scheduled time Friday to Tuesday evening so he could leave for <LOCATION> Baghdad </LOCATION> early. <PERSON> Aziz </PERSON> did not explain his premature departure. On Saturday, <PERSON> Aziz </PERSON> met with Iranian Foreign Minister <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Akbar </PERSON> <PERSON> Velayati </PERSON> for direct talks, but the session soon shifted to indirect talks. The secretary-general and his special mediator, Swedish U.N. Ambassador <PERSON> Jan </PERSON> <PERSON> K. </PERSON> <PERSON> Eliasson </PERSON>, shuttled between the Iranian and <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> delegations in separate rooms.
