<HEAD>Union Leader Slams Labor's Swing To Center</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MAUREEN JOHNSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BLACKPOOL, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The leader of <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s transit workers union warns that the <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, by moving to the center to broaden its appeal, could jeopardize its standing with its strongest supporters. `` They want our money and our strength, but they fear our power,'' <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Todd </PERSON>, head of the 1.25 million-member Transport and <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ' </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>, said Tuesday night during a meeting at the party's annual conference. `` There is a real division in the party which needs to be bridged as a matter of urgency,'' he said. <PERSON> Todd </PERSON>'s broadside marked the first serious public clash at the weeklong conference, which party leader <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Kinnock </PERSON> regards as a key step toward the adoption of a wholesale review of Labor policies. <PERSON> Todd </PERSON> controls one-fifth of the voting strength of the policy-making conference through a system under which the bosses of the <ORGANIZATION> Trades </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, the national labor federation, wield huge blocks of votes allocated according to membership. The arrangement dates back to the turn of the century when the unions founded the party. In the 1920s, <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> overtook the centrist Liberals to become, along with the currently governing Conservatives, one of <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s two major parties The first post-World War II Labor government founded the welfare state and set up the free <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>. Earlier in the conference, which ends Friday, <PERSON> Todd </PERSON> and other top union chiefs used their block votes to ensure <PERSON> Kin