nks, missiles and other heavy weapons passed the reviewing stand on truck-drawn trailers. Since <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON>'s death, <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>'s annual commemoration of the 1973 war has been limited to a televised speech by <PERSON> Mubarak </PERSON> on Oct. 6, the anniversary of the capture of <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> positions in the occupied <LOCATION> Sinai </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peninsula </LOCATION> that constituted <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>'s only success in four wars with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. No explanation was given for either the decision to have a parade this year or moving the celebration forward a day. The Oct. 6 parade became a tradition under <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON>, who watched the displays dressed in a resplendent military uniform. On the day he died, <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> wore a white, gold-braided uniform with high boots. <PERSON> Mubarak </PERSON>, a former fighter pilot, was dressed in an air force uniform on that day. It was his last public appearance in military uniform. On Wednesday, he wore a blue suit and mirrored sunglasses.
