d for 14 days. In addition, the supermarket chain will issue 1.6 million $ 1 coupons which will be redeemable on purchases of $ 10 or more at eastern <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> stores. The distribution dates for these coupons will be announced later. The coupons will be included in newspaper inserts and mailers delivered to households and in advertising circulars available at <ORGANIZATION> Stop </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Shop stores. <ORGANIZATION> Stop </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Shop operates 60 stores in the state. `` I urge consumers to take full advantage of this settlement by cutting out the coupons and redeeming them,'' <PERSON> Shannon </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Stop </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Shop also agreed to donate $ 100,000 in high-protein food to the <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Massachusetts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Food </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> and to reimburse the state $ 200,000 in litigation costs.
