<DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Military street patrols killed seven more looters in <LOCATION> Rangoon </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Mandalay </LOCATION>, bringing the number of people slain since the Sept. 18 military coup to about 440, the state radio reported Wednesday. <LOCATION> Rangoon </LOCATION> radio said the shootings occurred Tuesday. It and other official media have described most of those killed since the coup as looters or other `` destructive elements.'' Soldiers are imposing strict rules against public gatherings and looting. Vendors, gamblers and others who once crowded the sidewalks of <LOCATION> Rangoon </LOCATION> have disappeared. Civil servants and factory workers reported to their jobs for the third day but many left by early afternoon, apparently because of a lack of work in ministries and state enterprises crippled by a long general strike. All government employees were ordered back to work Monday under threat of dismissal. Two new youth organizations, the <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Youth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Federation </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> All </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burma </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Youth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organizations </ORGANIZATION>, registered as political parties Wednesday with a commission that is to supervise elections. The political leanings of the two groups were not immediately known. Three main opposition political parties have registered _ the <ORGANIZATION> Democracy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democracy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democracy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> _ but have not said whether they will particip