<HEAD>Ex-Wife: Chambers Killed Bean During Fight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEENE, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Former <PERSON> Marlow </PERSON> police chief <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON> killed his drinking buddy with a hatchet when the man tried to protect <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON>' estranged wife, she said in an interview published Wednesday. As he lay dying outside Chambers' home on Sept. 15, 1978, <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> <PERSON> Bean </PERSON>, then 25, looked at <PERSON> Deborah </PERSON> <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON>, told her to take care of his children, and said he loved his wife, <PERSON> Sylvia </PERSON>, <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON> told The <ORGANIZATION> Keene </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sentinel </ORGANIZATION>. Chambers declined to comment on the account, referring the Sentinel's questions to his lawyer, <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Sisti </PERSON>, who also declined to comment. Since Bean's skeletal remains were unearthed in March in Chambers' front yard, <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON>, 36, has said only six words publicly about the case: `` I did not kill <PERSON> Russ </PERSON> <PERSON> Bean </PERSON>.'' He was arrested April 15. <PERSON> Sisti </PERSON> tried to bar the state from presenting <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON>'s testimony to a grand jury in May, questioning her competence and citing a history of psychiatric treatment <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON> testified to the grand jury that prosecutors asked to issue a murder indictment. The grand jury, whose proceedings are secret, returned no indictment, leaving Chambers a free man. He is living with a policeman-friend in <LOCATION> Hinsdale </LOCATION> and working as a logger, the job he held 10 years ago. Phones calls to the residence went unanswered. <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON> also could not be reached. Police, acting on tips from Chambers' relatives, began digging in his front yard on March 11. They told police that <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON>' father, <PERSON> Clifton </PERSON>, told them <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON> came to him one night 10