ference to an affair Bean and <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON> had had earlier. <PERSON> Wentworth </PERSON> told the paper that when Bean stepped between her and <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON>, Chambers picked up a hatchet and hit Bean several times in the head and once in the chest. She told the Sentinel that <PERSON> Chambers </PERSON> then forced her into his truck, threw her suitcases in back, and drove her the short distance to <LOCATION> Newell </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pond </LOCATION>, where he beat her again, threatened her and left. Again a motorist picked her up. `` If I can find whoever picked her up, I hope -LRB- <LOCATION> Wentworth </LOCATION> -RRB- told them something,'' Sgt. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Rondo </PERSON>, chief state police investigator in the case, told the Sentinel. Police investigated Bean's disappearance, but closed the case, assuming Bean abandoned his family.
