<HEAD>LTV Corp. Putting Steel Bar Division Up For Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Cleveland </LOCATION>, a subsidiary of Dallas-based <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, plans to sell its Ohio-based steel bar division as part of the parent company's reorganization under federal bankruptcy laws. `` The company had indicated several months ago that it did not intend to reorganize with what it considered marginally profitable operations,'' said <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Coyle </PERSON>, director of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> 27. <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has hired <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> to help find a qualified buyer for the division. <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> also recently helped <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> find a buyer _ <ORGANIZATION> Warren </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Consolidated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> _ for its <ORGANIZATION> Warren </ORGANIZATION> mill and its Republic Drainage Products plant in <LOCATION> Canton </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION>'s bar division employs about 5,400 salaried or hourly workers, and the union represents about 4,200, with 3,200 at <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> operations in <LOCATION> Canton </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Massillon </LOCATION>. Company representatives met Tuesday in <LOCATION> Canton </LOCATION> with public and union officials. `` There's always uncertainty and some apprehension. The company assured us it's their intention to sell to a purchaser with a commitment to keep it profitable and more profitable in the future,'' <PERSON> Coyle </PERSON> said. <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> executive vice president, said at a news conference following the meeting there was no deadline set for a sale. `` The process will necessarily take a considerable period of time,'' <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON> said. `` Precisely what that will be is impossible for us to forecast, but it is nothing that is going to happen tonight, next week or even next month.'' Separate management, marketing, sales, customer service, engineering and research operations already exist in the bar division, <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hoag </PERSON> said in a statement. `` The bar division is well positioned and prepared to operate apart from <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Hoag </PERSON> said. He described the division as a leading producer of high quality carbon and alloy steel bars. <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hay </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> chairman and chief executive officer, said the steel segment is trying to focus on flat-rolled and tubular products. `` We have concluded that <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> must focus its resources on its large, modern flat-rolled facilities in order to maintain a leadership position in production of high-quality, value-added steels for critical engineering applications,'' <PERSON> Hay </PERSON> said in a statement issued from <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION>.
