ANIZATION> subsidiary would acquire <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> and other Apex properties, including a <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION> ski resort, for cash and the assumption of debt at a discount. Among <ORGANIZATION> Horsham </ORGANIZATION>'s partners in the deal is <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Zell </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> investor whose burgeoning business empire includes <ORGANIZATION> Itel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Zell </PERSON> said recently that he and <ORGANIZATION> Horsham </ORGANIZATION> want <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> because they believe the refining and marketing business will be a steady money-maker during a period of anticipated low oil prices Under the timetable set by the bankruptcy court, the rival bids will be reviewed next week. A full hearing on the purchase will be held Oct. 31, when the judge could approve one of the proposals.
