<HEAD>SAS, Texas Air Sign Cooperation Pact</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: ADDS new 4th graf to UPDATE with no comment from Texas Air;
picks up 4th graf pvs bg'ng, Some say ...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARCY GORDON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A new $ 50 million agreement between <ORGANIZATION> Scandinavian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> System </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> is designed to strengthen the competitive positions of both companies, officials say. Separately, a report published today said <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> is holding discussions to sell its <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> air shuttle to developer <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>. According to unidentified sources quoted by The Wall Street Journal, the pricetag on the three-city shuttle is in the $ 200 million range. As evidence the shuttle is up for sale, Journal sources noted that planes and lounge areas have been refurbished, and attendants are getting new uniforms. The service is run by <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> declined comment on the Journal report, said <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>, a spokesman for the airline company. Representatives of Trump were n't immediately available for comment. Some say <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> might use the shuttle, which operates between <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, to help draw people to his hotel and casino properties in <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> already operates a helicopter service between <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. Under <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>'s agreement with <ORGANIZATION> SAS </ORGANIZATION>, the Scandinav