<HEAD>Zenith Gives List Of Stockholders</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electronics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> agreed to hand over a list of its stockholders to a group of dissident shareholders Wednesday and said the group's attempt to wage a proxy fight against <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION> management would not trigger the company's takeover defense <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION> agreed to give the list to <ORGANIZATION> Brookhurst </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> just before a hearing in <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chancery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> over the group's attempt to wage a proxy battle to pressure the company into putting itself up for sale Just 20 minutes into the hearing, <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION> also surrendered on the issue at stake in the proceeding: whether <ORGANIZATION> Brookhurst </ORGANIZATION>'s proxy solicitation would trigger <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION>'s `` poison pill'' takeover defense. <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Herrmann </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION>'s attorney, declared that the consent solicitation of Sept. 14 would not trigger the rights plan, even if 15 percent of the shareholders' proxies were obtained by <ORGANIZATION> Brookhurst </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>. This means <ORGANIZATION> Brookhurst </ORGANIZATION> is now free to solicit shareholder support in its efforts to replace some company directors and sell <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION>. Brookhurst, which owns 6.1 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION>'s stock, is proposing to reduce the board from 10 members to six and replace three of the six with its own candidates. <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION>, the only remaining <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> television maker, is incorporated in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION>, but based in <LOCATION> Glenview </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ill. </LOCATION>, north of <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>. The company has indicated its desire to remain independent, and until Wednesday had resisted giving the shareholder list to <LOCATION> Brookhurst </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION> has been fighting a losing battle against low-priced imported televisions. Despite the success of its highly regarded computers, <ORGANIZATION> Zenith </ORGANIZATION> suffered losses over the past three years, including a $ 19.1 million loss last year on sales of $ 2.36 billion.
</TEXT>
