<SECOND>BC-Auto Recall,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>VW Recalls 1,700 Late 1988 Jettas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TROY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Volkswagen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> States </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday said it was recalling about 1,700 late-1988 model Jetta cars to inspect and replace, if necessary, a brake vacuum unit. <ORGANIZATION> Volkswagen </ORGANIZATION> said it was possible the unit could separate during heavy braking, which would, in turn, diminish braking power. The company said in a news release it was aware of no accidents or injuries due to the problem. Owners of the vehicles are being notified by mail. Inspection and replacement of the unit, if necessary, would be free to the consumer.
